There have been many industries in Holymoorside. Before motorized transport a successful{Blacksmith} shop existed. Around 1820 a{Wheelright shop was opened. Other agricultural equipment made locally included{ {barrels}and{butterchurns.}
For several centuries processes connected with{lead smelting}were carried out. The local sandstones are of good quality and so Holymoorside had a thriving{quarrying}industry.
Today{farming}is the largest industry in the area. However the manufacture of{besoms}and{brooms}from local heather and birch still exists. The heather is gathered together and tied around a central birch stake to make good quality besoms.
